{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4782b35f-8194-4005-849d-f95c53dc2714","content":"Two things change when moving to xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changes\n\nMTP uses `--filter` with **different operators**. The VSTest `~` (contains) operator becomes a wildcard or property check:\n\n```bash\n# Old (VSTest / xUnit v2)\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# New (MTP / xUnit v3)\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~*IntegrationTests*&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nWith MTP, `~` means \"glob match\" and requires explicit `*` wildcards (it's not an implicit substring match like VSTest's `~`).\n\nAlternatively you can use the long-form `--treenode-filter` syntax:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n### 2. `Trait` → xUnit v3 attribute\n\nxUnit v3 dropped `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` in favor of built-in attributes. Update your test class:\n\n```csharp\n// Old:  [Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]\n// New:\n[Category(\"Smoke\")]\n```\n\nThe `[Category]` attribute is first-class in xUnit v3, and the `Category` filter property maps to it directly.\n\n### Summary of changes needed\n\n| Area | Old (v2 + VSTest) | New (v3 + MTP) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Attribute | `[Trait(\"Category\",\"Smoke\")]` | `[Category(\"Smoke\")]` |\n| Filter | `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke` | `FullyQualifiedName~*IntegrationTests*&Category=Smoke` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"881d1a95-5e00-4920-b850-b9ab36e6d142","outputTokens":443,"requestId":"340F:386B3C:5401C53:5C31766:69F3FC2B"},"id":"26a8d41f-3396-4f26-9cec-b74a2273dc33","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:04:52.600Z","parentId":"ec964167-01df-409b-b71f-28c3ca0f21bc"}
